Wash and dry all produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a 
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook 
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and peel @Carrot{3%ounce}; using a #peeler{}, shave carrot 
lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard 
core. Trim ends from @Persian Cucumber{1}; using a peeler, shave cucumber 
lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core. 
Discard core. Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince 
@Garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}. Finely chop 
@Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine carrot ribbons, cucumber ribbons, 
half the @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. 
Microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until 
ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, 
@Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tbsp}, remaining vinegar, and @water{2%tbsp}.

Heat a #large, dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Peanuts{1/2%ounce}, 
@Sugar{2%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring often, until water has 
evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer peanuts to a second small bowl. Wipe out pan.

Heat @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in pan used for peanuts over medium-high heat. Add half 
the @Ground Plant-Based Protein{9%ounce}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an 
even layer; cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces. Add ginger, garlic, and scallions; cook, stirring, 
until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat, then stir in sauce. Stir until thoroughly combined, ~{30-60%seconds}. 
Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{} to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the cilantro and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Season 
with @salt{} to taste.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Add plant-based protein on one side and pickled 
carrot and cucumber ribbons on opposite side. Top with candied peanuts and 
remaining cilantro. Serve.